[Event "DGT Clock Simul"]
[Site "Enschede NED"]
[Date "2008.04.02"]
[EventDate "2008.04.02"]
[Round "1"]
[Result "1-0"]
[White "Vladimir Kramnik"]
[Black "Jan Werle"]
[ECO "E06"]
[WhiteElo "2788"]
[BlackElo "2581"]
[PlyCount "75"]

1. d4 {Notes by IM Malcolm Pein.} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2
Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 a6 8. Qxc4 b5 9. Qc2 Bb7
10. Bd2 Ra7 {It's a brave man who takes on Kramnik in the
Catalan but I suppose Werle was comforted by at least knowing
what to expect. Ra7 looks odd but is normal here and defends
b7 and c7 while preparing Qa8.} 11. a3 Be4 12. Qc1 Nc6 13. e3
Qa8 14. Qd1 {Defending f3. Black must counter in the centre or
he will just have weaknesses on the c file and no play.} Nd5
15. Qe2 e5 16. Re1 {16. dxe5? Nxe5 17. Nxe5 Bxg2 and White
cannot recapture because of 18. Kxg2 Nf4+ 19. Kg1 Nxe2#
[mate]} 16... exd4 17. exd4 f5 18. Nc3 Nxc3 19. Bxc3 Bf6
{19... Qd8 20. Ne5 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Qd5+ 22. Qf3 Qxf3+ 23. Kxf3
Nxe5+ 24. dxe5 c5 25. e6, planning Ra1-d1-d7 with a clear
advantage.} 20. d5 {!} Bxc3 21. bxc3 Nd8 22. Rad1 Bxd5 23. Ng5
c6 {23... Bxg2 24. Qh5! h6 25. Re7 hxg5 26. Rdd7 [wins]}
24. Bxd5+ cxd5 25. Qd3 {25. Qa2} 25... h6 26. Nf3 f4
{26... Nf7 27. Nh4 Ng5!?} 27. Nh4 {!} fxg3 28. hxg3 Nf7
29. Nf5 Ng5 {This comes very close to working but Kramnik
calculates further.} 30. Ne7+ Rxe7 31. Rxe7 Nf3+ 32. Kf1 d4
33. Qg6 Nh2+ 34. Ke1 {!} Nf3+ 35. Ke2 Ng1+ 36. Kf1 {! 36. Rxg1
Qf3+ 37. Kd2 Qxf2+ 38. Kd1 Qxg1+ wins for Black after 39. Kd2
Rf2+ 40. Kd3 Qb1+ 41. Kxd4 Qxg6} 36... Rxf2+ 37. Kxf2 Nh3+
38. Ke1 1-0